---
description: Formatting rules for the TypeScript workspace
globs:
  - typescript/packages/**/*
---


## Newlines, imports & indentation (`preferences-hooks`)

- **Indentation:** Use **4 spaces** everywhere (all `.ts` / `.tsx`
  files).
- **After imports:** Always put **exactly two blank lines** after the
  last `import` before the next top-level declaration, in **every**
  file.

## Interfaces, types & props — **order matters**

- **Do not reorder** existing fields in interfaces, type aliases, or
  component/hook props “for cleanup” or alphabetically unless the user
  asks. Treat the written order as **meaningful** (reading flow,
  grouping, or public API shape).
- **When adding** a field, extend the existing order: place it **next
  to related fields** or at the **end of the appropriate group** (e.g.
  required inputs together, optional tuning together, callbacks
  together)—never scatter without reason.
- **Mirror order where it helps:** `props` destructuring and `function
  Component({ a, b, c })` should follow the **same order as the props
  interface** when practical, so definition and usage stay easy to
  scan.
- **Related types** (e.g. `FooProps` and `UseFooProps`, or
  parent/child props) should use a **consistent field order** for
  overlapping concepts when both exist.

## Newlines & vertical rhythm (rest)

- **Functions/components (TSX & hooks):** One blank line immediately
  inside `{` before the first statement; blank line before `return`
  when there is preceding logic; blank line before the closing `}` of
  the function.
- **Interfaces:** Optional blank line after `{`; use blank lines to
  **group related fields**; within a group, order is **intentional**,
  not arbitrary.
- **JSX:** Use blank lines to separate **major sibling blocks**.
- **Utils:** Same import rule and 4-space indent; inside functions,
  blank lines between **clear logical steps** unless the function is
  large enough to warrant TSX-style spacing.

**For assistants:** Enforce **4 spaces**, **two blank lines after
imports**, and **preserve / extend interface & props ordering**—never
reshuffle member order without explicit instruction.
